article.headline: Vanderbilt 67, Tennessee 62
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Dainmon Gonner scored 27 points as Southeast Missouri beat Tennessee-Martin 75-68 Thursday night. Tennessee-Martin (4-16, 1-8 Ohio Valley Conference) cut Southeast Missouri's lead to 69-64 on a layup by Cleve Woodfork with 1:11 left, but two free throws by Terrick Willoughby put the Redhawks up for good. The Skyhawks pulled within three points three times in the second half but did not take the lead once. Willoughby scored 17 points for Southeast Missouri (10-10, 5-4), Reggie Golson added 15 points and 10 rebounds and Derek Winans scored 11. The Skyhawks struggled from 3-point range, hitting 2-of-10. Tennessee State was led in scoring by Woodfork with 21. Jared Newson scored his second-consecutive double-double with 19 points and 13 rebounds. Justin Smith added 10 points.
